Source: libtriton-jit
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: FlagTree Project <contact@flagos.io>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13),
               cmake,
               ninja-build,
               patchelf,
               python3-dev,
               nlohmann-json3-dev (>= 3.11.3)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/flagos-ai/libtriton_jit
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/flagos-ai/libtriton_jit
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/flagos-ai/libtriton_jit.git
Rules-Requires-Root: no
X-Build-Environment: This package is designed to be built in a CUDA container
 environment that provides the necessary SDK and Python packages:
 .
 - CUDA toolkit (>= 12.0) from nvidia/cuda base image
 - PyTorch (>= 2.5.0) and Triton (>= 3.1.0) via pip
 - pybind11 via pip, nlohmann-json via system package
 - fmt 10.2.1 is downloaded via CMake FetchContent at build time
 .
 The Build-Depends listed above are for the Debian packaging tools only.
 CUDA and Python dependencies are provided by the container environment.

Package: libtriton-jit
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Triton JIT runtime library
 libtriton_jit is a C++ library providing Triton JIT runtime functionality.
 It enables just-in-time compilation of Triton kernels for GPU acceleration.
 .
 This package contains the shared library.

Package: libtriton-jit-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         libtriton-jit (= ${binary:Version})
Conflicts: libfmt-dev
Description: Triton JIT runtime library - development files
 libtriton_jit is a C++ library providing Triton JIT runtime functionality.
 It enables just-in-time compilation of Triton kernels for GPU acceleration.
 .
 This package contains the development files (headers and CMake configs).
